== Roasted Veggies ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Cut @broccoli{8%ounce} florets into bite-size pieces if necessary. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @honey{2%teaspoon}, and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}; set aside.

Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}. (For 4 servings, use 2 #baking sheets{}; roast potatoes on top rack and broccoli on middle rack.)

After 10 minutes, carefully toss broccoli on empty side of baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper, and continue to roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Creamy Mustard Sauce ==

> We like serving up sides of roasted potatoes and broccoli for extra dipping, but if you broke out the spoon to scrape up leftover sauce, we wouldn't judge.

== Chicken Schnitzel ==

Meanwhile, place @panko breadcrumbs{½%cup}, lemon zest, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} in a #large zip-close bag{}. Season with @salt{1%tsp} (we used 1 tsp; 2 tsp for 4 servings) and @pepper{}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}.

Place @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} in a #medium bowl{}; add chicken and turn to coat.

Place coated chicken in #zip-close bag{} with panko mixture and seal to close. Shake until chicken is evenly coated.

> TIP: You may need to move chicken around in bag, pressing with your hands, to spread out panko and make it stick.

  Swap in chicken for pork.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of oil in a #large, heavy-bottomed pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of panko sizzles when added to pan, add chicken.

> TIP: Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cook until panko is golden and chicken is cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: For thicker pork chops, cook 1-2 minutes more.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== To Serve ==

Divide chicken, potatoes, and broccoli between plates. Serve with lemon wedges on the side and creamy mustard sauce for dipping or drizzling.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.